        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>erosion protection works [300006136], hydraulic structures by function [300006112], hydraulic structures [300006073], single built works by function [300004894], single built works by specific type [300004795], single built works (built environment) [300004790], Single Built Works (hierarchy name) [300004789], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Structures extending from the shore into a body of water and built to influence current or protect the entrance to a harbor or river from shoaling. For similar structures built to control or direct seashore erosions, use "groins (erosion protection works)"; use "wing dams" when such erosion control structures occur along banks of rivers or streams.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Estructura que se extiende desde la costa al interior de la masa de agua y que ha sido construida para influir en la corriente o proteger la entrada a los puertos o ríos de los bancos de arena. Para estructuras similares construidas para controlar o dirigir la erosión costera, use "arista de encuentro (obra de protección de erosión)"; use "escollera" cuando la estructura de control erosivo se encuentra a lo largo de los bancos de los ríos o corrientes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor bouwwerken die zich uitstrekken vanaf de kust of oever het open water in, om de stroming te beïnvloeden of om te voorkomen dat de toegang tot een haven of een rivier dichtslibt. Gebruik 'strandhoofden' voor soortgelijke bouwwerken die zijn opgeworpen om erosie van het strand te beperken of te sturen; gebruik 'vleugeldammen' voor erosiebeschermingswerken langs de oevers van rivieren of stromen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052374/Polytechnisch woordenboek En-Ne (1991)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>自岸邊延伸入水域中的結構物，其功用為影響水流或預防港口或河口之淺化。為控制或管理海岸侵蝕的類似結構物，稱為「丁壩（海岸屏障物）」；沿河岸或溪岸所築，以控制侵蝕的類似結構，則稱為「丁壩（河岸屏障物）」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
